headline: Two Full-Time Jobs Are Becoming The New Normal For Nearly Half A Million Americans
summary: The number of Americans holding two full-time jobs reached 476,000, marking the second-highest level on record. The figure trails only December 2025’s all-time peak of 488,000. The trend represents a dramatic shift in the U.S. labor market, according to data shared by The Kobeissi Letter. Dual full-time employment has doubled since 2020, surpassing the dot-com bubble peak of 416,000 workers in July 2000. headline: AI Weekly: Pentagon warns Anthropic, Disney unhappy with Bytedance
summary:
STORY: From the Pentagon warning Anthropic to Disney's Bytedance threat, this is AI Weekly.

:: AI Weekly

The Pentagon could end its relationship with Anthropic, according to a report in Axios.

It's said to be unhappy with the AI firm's restrictions on how the U.S. military uses its models.

The Pentagon wants the military to use Anthropic's tools for what it calls "all lawful purposes," including in weapons development and battlefield operations.

But Axios said Claude maker Anthropic hasn't agreed to those terms and the Pentagon is getting fed up after months of negotiations.

Bytedance will take steps to stop the unauthorized use of intellectual property on its new AI video generator.

The Chinese firm made the announcement following legal threats from U.S. studios, including Disney.

Seedance 2.0 was released last week and videos made on it have gone viral in China.

But a source told Reuters Disney accused the Chinese firm of using its characters to train and power Seedance without permission.

The AI Impact Summit kicked off in India to showcase the country's AI ambitions.

India's Prime Minister Narendra Modi opened the event, attended by tech heavyweights like Google CEO Sundar Pichai and more.

Indian leaders believe massive investments are coming to the country thanks to AI.

India's IT minister Ashwini Vaishnaw spoke at the Impact summit. 

"So far, whatever investment commitments we have seen, it looks like in the coming two years, we should be seeing more than $200 billion worth investment across the five layers of AI stack."

OpenAI warned U.S. lawmakers about the actions of Chinese AI startup DeepSeek.

A memo seen by Reuters showed the Sam Altman-led firm believes DeepSeek has tried to replicate U.S. models and use them for their own training.

The technique is known as distillation, where older AI models evaluate the quality of answers coming from a newer model - which effectively transfers the older version's learnings.

DeepSeek and its parent company High-Flyer didn't respond to Reuters' requests for comment.

And an Albanian actor is suing the country's government for using her image to play an AI character called 'Diella'.

Anila Bisha said she never gave consent to be portrayed as one of the world's first AI-generated "virtual ministers” - and she wants $1 million in damages.

Bisha says she allowed her likeness to be used last year to create an AI-powered virtual assistant for a government website, but not as a virtual politician on the prime minister’s team.

The Albanian government has denied any wrongdoing.
